---
title: "Blessing Letter: Dolly Parton"
subtitle: "The Woman Who Wrote the Anthem"
date: 2026-03-18
letter_type: "Blessing"
recipient: "Dolly Parton"
tags: ["blessing-letter", "music", "imagination-library", "worker-dignity"]
---

Dear Ms. Parton,

I listen to "9 to 5" every single day while I work.

The original. The Pitbull remix. Both. On rotation.

Not as background noise — as fuel. As a reminder of why I'm doing what I'm doing.

And in the Pitbull version — when you talk about your mother — it gets me every single time.

That part moves me to tears. Every. Single. Time.

Because that's who I'm building this for. The people who do the work with dignity, and deserve to keep more of what they earn.

I've been pouring cups of ambition for nine years now, building something I hope would make you — and your mama — proud.

---

## WHAT I'VE BUILT

My name is Jonathan Jones. I'm a 53-year-old father of eight, ARNG veteran, and the founder of Liana Banyan — a cooperative platform where workers keep 80% of what they earn.

I built a platform where that doesn't happen. **Cost + 20%.** Workers keep 80%. No middlemen extracting value. No algorithms pushing wages down. No "gig economy" that's really just exploitation with an app.

When someone cooks a meal for their neighbor, they keep $4 of every $5.
When someone makes a craft, they keep 80%.
When someone provides a service, they keep 80%.

The platform takes 20% to operate — and that's it. Transparent. Fair. The way it should be.

---

## WHY I'M WRITING TO YOU

I'm not asking you to run anything. You've got the Imagination Library to grow and a thousand other ways you're already changing the world. I know you funded the Moderna vaccine research without telling anyone. I know you've given away more books than most libraries own.

I'm writing because you wrote the anthem, and I wanted you to know someone's been listening.

Really listening.

---

## THE IMAGINATION LIBRARY CONNECTION

You give kids books so they can imagine a better future.
I'm trying to give adults a platform so they can build one.

Same philosophy: **Give people the tools. Trust them to do the rest.**

Your books don't come with strings attached. Neither does my platform. Join for $5 a year. Keep 80% of what you earn. No gotchas.

I'm trying to build a system that gives people more than smiles — it gives them a fair shake. A real path. A way to work hard AND get ahead, not just work hard and barely survive.

---

## THE PITBULL CONNECTION

I wrote to Pitbull too. Told him the same thing: your remix of "9 to 5" is on my daily playlist. Both of you — country royalty and Mr. Worldwide — saying the same thing about workers and dignity and not giving up.

If Liana Banyan succeeds, that song will have been part of why. It played in the background of nine years of building. It'll play in the background of the next nine too.

---

## WHAT I'M ASKING

Nothing expected. But if you know someone who could help — in food security, education, healthcare, or community development — tell them to contact me. You never have to speak with me at all. Just a word to someone in your network: *"Look at what this guy is building."* They can reach me directly at the number below.

The platform is at **Cephas.LianaBanyan.org** if you ever want to see it. Pick it apart. Tell me what's wrong with it. Or just know it exists, and that "9 to 5" was the soundtrack.

I've also written to Pitbull — because your "9 to 5" remix together says the same thing you said 44 years ago, and his SLAM schools prove he walks the walk — and to Jimmy Kimmel — because he stood in that hospital hallway waiting for news about his son Billy, just like I did for my son Ethan, and he uses his platform to fight for healthcare access. If you see anything worthwhile here, feel free to connect the dots I can't.

And if you ever want to be involved — in any way, at any level — there's a seat at the table. Not because I need your fame. Because you already understood the problem 44 years ago when you wrote the song. I'm just trying to build the solution.

**This invitation extends to anyone reading this.** If you know someone who could help, tell them about us.

---

With deep respect and gratitude,

**Jonathan R. Jones**
Founder & Crewman #6
Liana Banyan Corporation

Founder@LianaBanyan.com
406-578-1232

